	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I finally finished this quest the other night after about a month. By far the hardest part was the Dark Assassin, killed him 3 times, not an easy fight to say the least.<br><br>I started the quest by having a bard charm the barb, handed in the gold, got the potion then got out of Halas (I'm pretty kos there). Next I went to Tox, gave Jalen Goldsinger his 1k gold and the potion, in return I recieved the crystal of capturing.<br><br>Then I went to GFay, killed that wasp for awhile, Alicia never spawned. I then payed a few newbies to kill all the wasps they saw and about 30 mins later she poped. I had a 49 wizard come help and she dropped fairly easily. She did resist darkness quite a bit, however once it landed, she was cake.<br><br>Got the heart, got the crystal, went over to Everfrost, had a ranger track for the DA, first time we killed him it was one crazy fight.<br><br>The Dark Assassin is a level 50 rogue, quad hits for 145 and backstabs for 450. He also runs at just under jboot speed. <br><br>Had 6 people 45-55, fight took about 15 mins. He is pretty resistant to magic, Ice Comet didn't do much, about 1 in every 5 ebolts landed, Asystole landed once in about 6 tries. Splurt was the only reliable dot. <br><br>From what I was told after the fight he ate Chars like candy, so I'll assume his Fire Resistance is fairly low.<br><br>Second fight was much easier, just had a bard charm Ice Giants on him for about 30 mins and he finally died. Both times he dropped the Bloody Dagger (6/22 3str 3dex effect Disease Cloud, Rogue only).<br><br>Third fight was by far the easiest, brought a 50 ranger and a 50 bard. Ranger was able to ensanre him, it was over after that, took about 6 splurts, plus pet, the ranger, and bard beating on him before he went down. This time he finally dropped my Mantle.<br><br>Went over to Paineel, the Tourmented Soul is in the necro hall, on the second floor. Started with Amiable faction. Didn't want to take the chance of it not being high enough so I went into The Warrens for about an hour, killed Kobolds, and when I came out I was Kindly.<br><br>Handed in the Soul Trap and I have a new Mantle.<br><br>Pain in the ass quest but well worth it. I play on a pvp server so most of my equipment slots are dedicated to resists. 10int in the shoulders is amazing.<br><br><br>Beholdr D'aestry<br>Guild Leader of Macabre<br>Vallon Zek<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
