	   <tr><td colspan=2>First thing I did was get the box. That is easy and everyone knows how to do it.<br><br>Second, I went to gfay. I brought up a pet and started running all over the zone. Eventually Alania attacked me out of nowhere(I guess I got lucky there). Important notes on how to kill her. I am a 52 necro and it took all my mana(I did not lich during the fight). You should open with dooming then fear her. Then DISPELL her or your pet will take a beating from her damage sheild. After that splurt and sit down. Just reapply dark and fear and splurt. I timed darkness so that it never wore off. You might want to mem screaming terror too. This is in case fear wears off towards the end. She WILL try to heal herself and fear will not interupt the cast.<br><br>Third part for me was to kill the dark assassin. I would like to take this moment to say that jboots will not cut it =P . I tried this first with myself and a 51 shaman. We were not fully ready but decided to try anyway. Since I didn't have sow he started hitting me fast and hard. I feigned and the shaman starting running. My pet and his did around 10% of damage in the 1 min the fight was going. We regrouped and called in extra help. We had me(52 necro), 51 pally, 51 shaman, 40 SK, 54 mage, and a ranger that helped track him down(assassin was standing still after the first attempt). This all went down in everfrost. The dark assassin will pass by the 2 goblin camp every 5 min(SW corner) when he is up. We had no need for pet kiting this time. All that we did was send pets and tanks then heal them. All in all we only lost one pet in the fight. <br><br>Fourth, I group-quested the crystal with the shaman. This is easy to do as well.<br><br>I cast identify on all parts to be safe and then combined for the soul trap. After that I spent about 3-4 hours raising faction with paineel. What I did was kill all the green Sentinels in tox, Algilthin(sp?), and Vinlay(sp?). I killed about 8 sentinels, the fisherman 4 times, vinlay 3 times, and also the Fathomwalker lady once. I also did the batwing and snakefang quest 40 times. I just bearly made kindly and I gave the trap to the tormented soul and got my mantle of souls.<br><br>Since the mantle is no drop does anyone else suspect it to be part of another quest? I just don't like he idea of giving the mantle to somebody to see if anything happens.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
